<TITLE> Stocks climb as rate cut hopes intact </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tue Sep 11, NEW YORK (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Stocks rose on Tuesday, as rate-sensitive banking stocks gained on hopes that Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke will do nothing to dim hopes for an interest-rate cut when he delivers a speech this morning. A string of positive headlines boosted biotechnology stocks, including ImClone Systems Inc (IMCL.O: Quote, Profile, Research), which jumped after German drug maker Merck KGaA (MRCG.DE: Quote, Profile, Research) said ImClone's Erbitux cancer drug improves overall survival in lung cancer patients when paired with platinum-based chemotherapy. Western Digital Corp (WDC.N: Quote, Profile, Research), the No. 2 disk-drive maker, lifted its earnings and revenue forecast late on Monday on improved demand. Bear Stearns lifted its rating on Western Digital on Tuesday. Bernanke is speaking at 11 a.m. (1500 GMT) in Berlin on the topic of global imbalances. The Fed chairman said last week the U.S. central bank is set to act to limit the impact of financial turmoil on the economy, but will not bail out investors who made poor decisions. On Monday several Fed speakers warned financial turmoil has increased the risks facing the U.S. economy. Bernanke "has to reiterate that he's going to do what it takes to make up some ground if there is a chance of recession," said Rich Parker, head of trading at Stanford Group in New York. The Dow Jones industrial average (.DJI: Quote, Profile, Research) was up 102.10 points, or 0.78 percent, at 13,229.95. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index (.SPX: Quote, Profile, Research) was up 10.70 points, or 0.74 percent, at 1,462.40. The Nasdaq Composite Index (.IXIC: Quote, Profile, Research) was up 20.82 points, or 0.81 percent, at 2,579.93. Among banking shares, Citigroup Inc (C.N: Quote, Profile, Research) was the biggest gainer, up 1 percent to $45.76. Shares of Wells Fargo (WFC.N: Quote, Profile, Research) were up 1.9 percent to $35.81 on the NYSE. Western Digital shares were up 5.3 percent $23.60 on the NYSE. Nabi Biopharmaceuticals (NABI.O: Quote, Profile, Research) agreed to sell its biologics business to a German firm, sending its shares surging. Shares of Sepracor Inc (SEPR.O: Quote, Profile, Research) were the biggest percentage gainer on the Nasdaq after news it signed an agreement with GlaxoSmithKline (GSK.L: Quote, Profile, Research) for the UK drug maker to market Sepracor's insomnia drug Lunesta outside the United States. Sepracor shares were up 5.7 percent to $28.96. Nabi stock climbed 21.2 percent to $4.17 and ImClone surged 21.5 percent to $46.10. Tuesday marks the sixth anniversary of the September 11, 2001 attacks on the United States, including the destruction of the World Trade Center that closed the New York Stock Exchange for four sessions, the longest hiatus since the run-up to World War One. In a sign recession may not be on the horizon, staffing services firm Manpower Inc (MAN.N: Quote, Profile, Research) said US employers remain confident about hiring for the fourth quarter. McDonald's Corp (MCD.N: Quote, Profile, Research) shares led gains on the Dow after the fast food chain reported higher August sales at restaurants open at least 13 months. Shares of McDonald's were up 3.2 percent to $51.76 on the NY
